<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="py-12 bg-gray-50 border-t mb-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
      <details class="rounded-md border bg-white p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is this free?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Yes — you can sign up and start immediately. No credit card required.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-md border bg-white p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">What can I study?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Add legal <strong>cases</strong> and <strong>provisions</strong> (linked to their <strong>Acts</strong>). More card types can be added over time.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-md border bg-white p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">How are review times chosen?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Brief/Case uses spaced repetition. Your ratings (Again/Hard/Good/Easy) adapt future due times so difficult cards resurface sooner.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-md border bg-white p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Can I come back to a session later?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Yes. Progress saves automatically. You can pause, return, or mark sessions completed and reopen them later.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
